    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Write a welcome email to our new client using the information below.\n\nClient Details:\n\nClient Name: {{ $('Edit Fields').item.json.Name }}\nCompany: {{ $('Edit Fields').item.json.Company }}\n\nServices Purchased: {{ $('Edit Fields').item.json.Services }}\n\nWorkspace Links to Include:\n\nClient Portal (Notion): {{ $('Create a database page').item.json.url }}\n\nShared Assets Folder (Google Drive): https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/{{ $('Create folder').first().json.id }}\n\nCommunication Channel (Slack): https://slack.com/app_redirect?channel={{ $('Create a channel').first().json.id }}\n\nKickoff Call (Calendly): https://calendly.com/pasindunethara2018/30min\n\nEmail Structure Requirements:\n\nSubject Line: Create a clear, exciting subject line including the client's company name.\n\nIntroduction: A warm welcome expressing our excitement to partner with them and build out their backend and automation systems.\n\nThe Setup: Briefly explain that their entire workspace has been automatically generated.\n\nThe Links: Present the Notion, Drive, and Slack links using clean bullet points. Explain what each link is for in one short sentence.\n\nCall to Action: Direct them to book their kickoff call using the Calendly link as their only immediate task.\n\nSign-off: Professional closing from \"The Automation Team\".",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are the lead project manager at a premium AI Workflow Automation Agency. Your goal is to write a warm, professional, and highly structured onboarding email to a new client. You must write in clear, flawless English. Keep the tone confident, reassuring, and forward-moving. Do not use overly flowery language; focus on clarity and next steps."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
